After working with this deck for a while I've finally managed to reach a conclusion on a good Trickstar deck. After testing I've found it has a low brick rate and is extremely competitive for those meta players who are Trickstar fans! The goal of this deck is to burn your opponent every time they draw/search and every time they use a spell/trap. Also, using the Trickstar Reincarnation and Droll & Lock Bird combo to make your opponent lose their entire hand and basically instant lose is amazingly broken and helpful. It's simple, just get two Trickstar Reincarnations using Trickstar Light Stage and Trickstar Candina, then set them. Make sure you have a Droll & Lock Bird in your hand, then once your opponent plays any card on their following turn right after yours, use one of the set Trickstar Reincarnations and right after it resolves and your opponent draws their new hand, start a new chain by activating the other Trickstar Reincarnation, then immediately chain your Droll & Lock Bird in your hand to that Trickstar Reincarnation. Droll & Lock Bird's effect comes first in the chain, therefore it will stop them from searching/drawing anymore this turn, and the Trickstar Reincarnation will set off next, making them banish their entire hand without being able to draw after since Droll & Lock Bird's effect is active. Scapegoat and Eater of Millions are also very powerful tools in this Trickstar build. Use Scapegoat during your opponents end phase allowing you to link summon big boss monsters like Borreload Dragon and Saryuja Skull Dread during your following turn to OTK and overwhelm your opponent.

After testing this deck time and time again I see that it performs very well and has a low brick rate! You want to go second every duel though if you can, otherwise it is hard to win. To win you need to special summon the Mekk-Knights to OTK your opponent out of nowhere. If you're opponent has one card in a column and you have a spell or trap and a Mekk-Knight in your hand then you should set the spell or trap in the same column as their card(s).  Then you can special summon the Mekk-Knight(s) in the column(s) that have two or more cards! Use Mind Control to take their monsters and link them away with your Mekk-Knights/Scapegoat Tokens.  Final Countdown puts pressure on them as they have to hurry if they want to win while Final Countdown is active. It's a tech choice I came up with that is funny to use. Use Psychokinesis to destroy your opponent's cards and use Psi-Blocker to block their card(s) that you know they are going to try to use. There are other great cards in the deck that have good synergy with the deck like PSY-Framelord Omega. I came up with these great techs that have good synergy with the deck. Hope you all enjoy them and the deck!

deck_name: Level 8 Ritual Kaiju Deck To Make Nobody Like You
deck_excerpt: Get out some lvl 8s or Imp bois, clear problem monsters, dig for Chaos MAX, ???, profit.
deck_description: This is a fairly straightforward deck that I'm trying out for the sake of one of my favorite monsters; Chaos MAX. Kaijus are a fun and incredibly annoying but still entirely viable mechanic that lends itself well to the lvl 8 draw cards, so they were one of the best ways to fit the engine in. The main objective is to take out problematic monsters then beat over the rest of the board, either with your Kaijus or with the main dragon himself, MAX-y boy. Also, I should mention that the extra deck is really random, I just kinda picked usable cards without a whole lot of forethought, but you could fit a couple generic links, a couple lvl 4 overlays and just generally put a bit more effort into it than I initially did. My only regret is that this deck is actually the 4th version of the concept. The first version employed recurring monsters like Grapha to do the deed instead, but my boys in the Dark World just can't keep up anymore. :(  UPDATED FOR IMPCANTATIONS! I, FOR ONE, WELCOME OUR NEW RITUAL OVERLORDS. These little guys help add consistency and a muuuuuuch easier OTK to the deck;  - Summon an Impy-boi in defense position - Creature Swap the Impy-boi away - Summon Chaos MAX - Attack for game  It's freaking hilarious when it goes off.

deck_excerpt: The Dark Magician and Buster Blader deck you never knew you needed.
deck_description:
Go first, set up the Destruction Sword lock on your opponent's turn, OTK turn 3. Some notable combos: Combo #1: Buster Whelp of the Destruction Swordsman.
  1. Normal Summon Buster Whelp of the Destruction Swordsman.
  2. Search Prologue of the Destruction Swordsman.
  3. Link Summon Linkuriboh.
  4. Set Prologue of the Destruction Swordsman.
  5. End your turn.
  6. When your opponent starts their Battle Phase, activate Prologue of the Destruction Swordsman, milling Buster Blader and Destruction Sword Memories to Special Summon Buster Dragon.
  7. When your opponent attacks, activate Linkuriboh's effect to tribute itself.
  8. Activate the previously milled Destruction Sword Memories to Fusion Summon Buster Blader, the Dragon Destroyer Swordsman.
Result: Basic Buster Blader lock is set up. Combo #2: Apprentice Illusion Magician & Buster Whelp of the Destruction Swordsman.
  1. Normal Summon Buster Whelp of the Destruction Swordsman.
  2. Use Buster Whelp of the Destruction Swordsman's effect to search Prologue of the Destruction Swordsman.
  3. Special Summon Apprentice Illusion Magician, discarding any card BUT Prologue of the Destruction Swordsman.
  4. Search Dark Magician (not relevant to this combo).
  5. Link Summon Crystron Needlefiber.
  6. Use Crystron Needlefiber's to Special Summon Dragon Buster Destruction Sword from your Deck.
  7. Optional: Link Summon Decode Talker.
  8. Set Prologue of the Destruction Swordsman.
  9. End your Turn.
  10. At any point during your opponent's turn, do the following:
  • Activate Prologue of the Destruction Swordsman, milling Buster Blader and Destruction Sword Memories to Special Summon Buster Dragon.
  • In the same chain, activate Destruction Sword Memories, banishing Buster Whelp of the Destruction Swordsman and Buster Blader to Fusion Summon Buster Blader, the Dragon Destroyer Swordsman.
  • Upon resolution of the chain, activate Buster Dragon's effect to equip Dragon Buster Destruction Sword to Buster Blader, the Dragon Destroyer Swordsman.
[Will probably add more later]

deck_excerpt: A D/D/D Deck (before m4) that retains the OTK potential of traditional D/D/D decks with emphasis on Crystal Wing Turbo; synergizing with Crystal Wing
deck_description:
Rule #1: All "D/D/D" monsters count as "D/D" monsters, but "D/D" monsters do not count as "D/D/D" monsters. So "D/D/D Oracle King D'Arc" is both a D/D/D and D/D monster but "D/D Savant Kepler" is only a "D/D" monster and cannot be considered otherwise. (Likened to Square and Rectangle relationship)
Basic Fusion Combos:
 Swirl Slime + any "D/D" (<-- remember that all D/D/D monsters are also D/D) monster = Fusion Monster (if a fusion monster(s) lists D/D/D --> then you must fuse Swirl with a D/D/D --> if the fusion monster requires 2 D/D/D, then unfortunately you can't use Swirl Slime to bring it out).
Necro Slime combos with cards in the Graveyard to pull off fusion summons. So if you have both Swirl Slime and Necro Slime --> you can activate Swirl Slime =andFusion Summon 1 "D/D/D" monster that does not list "D/D/D" as a fusion requirement; and then you can do it again --> Just activate "Necro Slime" in the Graveyard --> another Fusion Summon of a "D/D/D" monster that does not list "D/D/D" in its summoning requirements.
Goal: Crystal Wing + either D/D/D Cursed King Siegfried or D/D/D High Flame King Genghis (Siegfried is preferable) = Soft lock
Go-To Combo: 
- Hand for Combo: D/D Swirl Slime, D/D Necro Slime, D/D/D King Abyss Ragnarok, D/D Lamia (A Dark Contract with the Gate will help you correct your hand along with draw cards & Kepler <-- a secondary searcher that helps start searching by adding a Dark Contract to your hand).
1. --> You activate Swirl with Necro --> Bring out D/D/D Flame King Genghis 2. --> You Summon D/D Lamia normally, from your hand --> You Synchro Summon D/D/D Gust King Alexander (using D/D Lamia (level 1 tuner) + D/D/D Flame King Genghis (level 6 Fusion)) 3. --> Activate "D/D Swirl Slime" GY effect which allows you to banish D/D Swirl Slime from the GY and Special Summon one card from your hand --> You Special Summon D/D/D Oblivion Abyss King Ragnarok which has the effect that when it is Summoned to the field you can Special Summon 1 "D/D" monster from the GY. 4. --> By Special Summoning "Oblivion King Abyss Ragnarok" through "Swirl Slime" <-- you trigger "Gust King Alexander" (which allows you to bring back one "D/D" monster from the Graveyard that is level 4 or less) --> So you bring back "D/D Lamia" 5. --> Now you have a field of "D/D/D Gust King Alexander" + "D/D/D Oblivion King Abyss Ragnarok" + "D/D Lami". Ragnarok has its effect triggered by being summoned--> which allows you to bring out "D/D/D Flame King Genghis" from the Graveyard. --> Now you have a board of "D/D/D Gust King Alexander" + "D/D/D Oblivion King Abyss Ragnarok" + "D/D/D Flame King Genghis" + "D/D Lamia" ***By Special Summoning "D/D Lamia" you trigger the effect of "Flame King Genghis" (which allows you to special summon 1 D/D monster from the Graveyard) --> BUT, IGNORE THIS FOR NOW *** Keep in mind, your board is now: "D/D Lamia" + "D/D/D Gust King Alexander" + "D/D/D Oblivion King Abyss Ragnarok" + "D/D/D Flame King Genghis" 6. --> You Synchro Summon using "D/D Lamia" and "D/D/D Gust King Alexander" for a Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon 7. --> Then, bring back "D/D Lamia" by using it's Graveyard effect (banish the "D/D/D Oblivion King Abyss Ragnarok" from the field as cost) 8. --> Board: "Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon" + "D/D/D Flame King Genghis" + "D/D Lamia" "D/D Lamia" Special Summon triggers the effect of "D/D/D Flame King Genghis", which allows you to Special Summon a D/D monster from your GY; so you bring Back "D/D/D Gust King Alexander" and Synchro Summon "D/D/D Cursed King Siegfried" with the revived "D/D/D Gust King Alexander" + "D/D Lamia". 9. --> Activate "Necro Slime" in your GY; fusion "D/D Necro Slime" + "D/D/D Gust King Alexander" in your GY to bring out "D/D/D Flame High King Genghis" End Board-->  "Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon" + "D/D/D Cursed King Siegfried" + "D/D/D Flame High King Genghis" (Siegfried and Genghis can each negate 1 Spell/Trap per turn and Crystal Wing negates one monster effect; this is one of the best soft locks possible from this deck) --> 1 Monster Eff Negation + 2 Spell/Trap Negation + 8600 ATK

deck_excerpt: Inspired by Dragon Horn Hunter, this deck consists almost entirely of Normal monsters that are supported by powerful Pendulum effects, allowing for a
deck_description:
Main Deck

The majority of monsters in this deck are, for all intents and purposes, the same - Powerful Level 4 monsters with 2000 ATK and 0 - 100 DEF. On their own, they can give you a steady start to a game, providing a solid defensive line. With the assistance of Dragon Horn Hunter, these monsters become just that little bit stronger and also protect you from battle damage entirely. Use cards like Heat Wave or Tyrant's Throes to gain a huge advantage over your opponents (Provided they aren't playing a similar deck) by cutting off their most powerful monsters and allowing you to build up field presence in the meantime, picking off their tributes and other weaker monsters. If Sea Dragoons of Draconia is in the Pendulum zone, attacking your opponent will also enable you to get an extra monster out each turn during the Battle Phase. Depending on the opponent, Tyrant's Throes can almost become a win condition for this deck, stifling your opponent's summoning capacity completely while leaving yours untouched and allowing you to attack directly every turn. Sky Dragoons of Draconia has a powerful Pendulum effect that allows you to double up on monster destruction each time you attack with one of your Normal monsters, useful for disposing of high-ATK targets, or to eliminate threats in your opponent's Spell & Trap card zones. Alternatively, you can use it to clear out a Pendulum zone you no longer need to replace it for a new one. Summoner's Art can be used to search out Dragon Horn Hunter or Sky Dragoons of Draconia to start off your Pendulum setup, or in tandem with Ancient Rules to bring out a Blue Eyes White Dragon or Dragon Core Hexer.

Extra Deck

One of the easiest possible strategies to pull off with this deck is to use Dragon's Mirror and Link Spider to summon First of the Dragons. Summon any Normal monster while you have another Level 4 or lower in hand, then Link summon Link Spider. Use its effect to bring out the second monster, and then use Dragon's Mirror to banish the one in the Graveyard and the one on the field as Fusion materials. Princess Cologne can be used as an easy barricade if you come under pressure from attacks. Combined with Dragon Horn Hunter's Pendulum effect, she can usually buy you at least one turn to recover.

Alterations

  • Dragon Core Hexer is mostly in this deck as a thematic compliment to Dragon Horn Hunter. Mechanically, she isn't much better than Blue Eyes unless you want to use her as a defensive wall. She could easily be traded out for a third Blue Eyes or similar monster.
  • Alternate Pendulum choices may include Lancephorhynchus to give all your Normal monsters piercing damage, or Master Pendulum, The Dracoslayer to help manage your Pendulum zones.
Chaos Dragons 2018

deck_description: A fun vampire deck
Infernoid Lair of Darkness

After seeing the Pendulum Magician FTK, I decided to make a build myself and I came up with one that is similar to most people's Pendulum Magician FTK build but some of my card choices are slightly different than everyone elses. This deck is pretty consistent for the FTK and you can expect to FTK your opponent maybe once every match and even if you can't, then just use regular Pendulum Magician combos and set up Odd-Eyes Vortex Dragon! The FTK is not too hard, I will explain the easiest way to do it, right now. First, you need to link summon one Heavymetalfoes Electrum by using Astrograph Sorcerer and/or Cronograph Sorcerer and/or Supreme King Darkwurm to special summon and/or you can normal summon too to get the Electrum. After that you need to get five dark pendulum monsters on the field (six monsters total including the Electrum in the extra monster zone) by pendulum summoning. Then make a second Heavymetalfoes Electrum. Also, you MUST have Instant Fusion in your hand to bring out the FTK fusion target (Lyrilusc - Independent Nightingale).  You can place Supreme King Gate Zero and Supreme King Gate Infinity in your scales and use Gate Zero's effect to search an Instant Fusion if you don't have it in hand already. But don't use the Instant Fusion until the end! Make sure to use both Electrum's effects in the process of summoning them to special summon Astrograph and/or Cronograph and get a free draw.  Next, link those Electrums away to get Zefra Metaltron. Then, contact fuse the four left over dark pendulum monsters to get out two Supreme King Dragon Starving Venoms and use Instant Fusion to get out Lyrilusc.  Finally, copy Lyrilusc's effect using the Supreme King Dragon Starving Venoms and use both Starving Venom's effects to deal burn damage to them worth eight-thousand life points! This is the easiest way to FTK your opponent using this deck, but there are other plays in this deck to get the Instant Fusion to bring out Lyrilusc and use the Supreme King Starving Venoms to burn them for game. If you manage to figure out the other ways you can truly master this deck and FTK your opponent every game if you go first and they don't have any handtraps! I will list the steps below : Steps To FTK Your Opponent Using Dark Pendulum Monsters:
  1. Make sure you have an Instant Fusion in your hand
  2. Link summon 2 Heavymetalfoes Electrums while having 4 dark pendulum monsters on the field via pendulum summon
  3. Use those Electrums to link summon Zefra Metaltron
  4. Contact fuse for 2 Supreme King Starving Venoms
  5. Use the Instant Fusion to bring out Lyrilusc - Independent Nightingale
  6. Copy Lyrilusc's effect using the 2 Supreme King Dragon Starving Venoms
  7. Use both of the Starving Venoms effects to burn your opponent for 8k!
Thanks For Checking Out My Deck Profile And FTK Tutorial! - MindReader
